<br>
1) If you have any base stats UNDER 75, bring them up to 75.<br>
<br>
2) STA will give you the most noticable bang for your bick: more STA = more Hit Points.  After fulfilling rule #1, dump as many points as you can into STA.<br>
<br>
3) If you ahve anything left after applying rules #1 and #2, put the rest of your points into AGI - AGI is hard to raise, primarily because Shaman FOCUS doesn't affect AGI.<br>
<br>
4) Stat points don't REALLY matter.  Sure, you can mon/max your effectiveness as a warrior by following the first three rules (above), but in the big picture it really doesn't matter that much.  There are two things that are REALLY important to a warrior:<br>
<br>
Level<br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
Equipment<br>
<br>
